post_text:
On August 24th the Greater Kansas City Suburban conference voted unanimously to allow fall sports to continue for students. As a member of the Suburban Conference, Fort Osage will continue to practice and participate with several safety protocols in place. Our complete fall sports guidelines for sporting contests can be found at: https://www.fortosage.net/Page/624

In order to accommodate additional parents/guardians, we have moved our Friday night FOHS football vs. Kearney from a home game to an away game. We will be traveling to Kearney with our football team and cheerleaders. Spectators will be limited to two guests per game day participant and tickets will be issued. Kearney will offer a live broadcast of the game for those not receiving tickets. More information will be shared on Friday on how to access that broadcast.

post_text:
2019-20 Grade Cards

This year Fort Osage has put the student report cards in the parent portal for you to view/print. If you have any problems or need a printed copy of the report card mailed to you, please contact your child’s school.

To access your child’s report card:

Log in to Infinite Campus Parent Portal. If you need help with your username and password please call your child’s school.

Go to the left side of the screen, Click MORE in the black box.

Click Student Reports

Select the Student

Select Report Report Card 2019/2020

Click Generate Report

Click Print. This will turn the report card into a pdf document you can view or print.

Detailed screen instructions, and instructions for students to view their own report cards, can be found at https://tinyurl.com/FortOsagePortalRC

post_text:
Fort Osage will continue providing breakfast and lunch for kids 18 and under throughout the summer. There are a few changes in our schedule for pick up of food items.

Next week you can pick up food on May 26, 27, and 29th (Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday) from 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Pick up on May 26 will include food for that day. Pick up on May 27 will have food for Wednesday and Thursday. Pick up on May 29th will include food for Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.

Starting on June 1 and running through July 3, meals can be picked up on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays from 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Monday's pick up will include food for Monday and Tuesday. Wednesday's pick up will include food for Wednesday and Thursday. Friday's pick up will include food for Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.

As a reminder our locations for pick up are Blue Hills, Buckner, Cler-Mont and Elm Grove Elementary Schools and Hawthorne Place apartments.

Information for the free breakfast and lunch program in July will be shared in late June.

post_text:
The following update on the Fort Discovery Program was shared with families yesterday:

The Fort Discovery childcare program will be open from 6:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. from July 6-August 14. Families who wish to enroll can do so online at https://app3.jackrabbitclass.com/regv2.asp?id=511849 . From July 6-July 24 those students enrolled in Fort Discovery will be required to attend the summer academy. You must register for both programs separately. During the summer academy, Fort Discovery will be offered for rising Kindergarteners-6th (if enough students enroll). Parents will be responsible for dropping off and picking up students from each site as transportation is not being provided.

Starting on July 27 Fort Discovery will be held at Blue Hills Elementary from 6:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. for all families enrolled. The cost will be $105 per week per child. A free breakfast and lunch will be provided.

We wanted to let you know of a change to the free breakfast/lunches starting tomorrow, April 27th.

Lunch will now include items that have been fully cooked, but will need to be re-heated prior to eating. Reheating instructions will be in each bag handed out and emailed to parents. These items include some of the students favorites such as chicken nuggets, burritos, mozzarella sticks, fries, corn dogs nuggets, and pizza crunchers.

As a reminder, pick up is on Mondays and Thursdays from 10:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. Monday's pick up will include food for Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday. Thursday's pick up will include food for Thursday, Friday, and Saturday. This is open to all children 18 and younger.

If your student was registered for the June administration, ACT reassigned them to a test site that will be open for the June administration. Students who wish to change their registrations to the July test date at our school will need to make the update in their registration account. This can be done free of charge through ACT. If you have any questions, please contact Krystal Brier, college adviser at kbrier@fortosage.net or your student's counselor.

Due to ongoing restrictions, the June summer school program will be very limited. At this time, we intend to provide a few online high school courses, including credit recovery opportunities. Students already enrolled in these courses will receive additional information in the next few weeks, and high school students may contact their counselor if they are interested in enrolling. post_text:
The Fort Osage Board of Education is pleased to announce three new administrators coming to Fort Osage for the 2020-2021 school year. Help us welcome them by leaving a message below.

Mr. Ryan Souza is the next Principal at Cler-Mont Elementary School. Souza will begin his duties effective July 1, 2020. Souza is replacing Mrs. Julie Stout who is retiring on June 30, 2020.

Ms. Jennifer Stotler is the next Principal at Indian Trails Elementary School. Stotler will begin her duties effective July 1, 2020. Stotler is replacing Mrs. Emily Cross who accepted the position of Assistant Superintendent for Educational Services at Fort Osage.

Mrs. Amy Cox is the next Principal and Parents as Teacher Coordinator at the Woodland Early Childhood Center. Cox will begin her duties effective July 1, 2020. Cox is replacing Mrs. Karen Harrach who is retiring on June 30, 2020.

post_text:
Good evening Rising Grade 5 Families!

It's time to mark your calendars for Rising Grade 5 Night at Fire Prairie! On Tuesday, April 14 beginning at 6:00 PM we will meet in the FP gym to provide you and your Rising Grade 5 Student information about FP! You will have an opportunity to:
learn more about fifth grade and FP,
meet fifth grade educators and staff,
ask questions,
tour the building, and
enjoy a free hot dog/chips meal!
We will begin promptly at 6:00 PM in the gym and our evening events will conclude at 7:15 PM. We look forward to seeing you on Tuesday, April 14 at 6:00 PM at FP! If you have any questions regarding this event, please call the FP office at 816-650-7158 or email me at sbaker@fortosage.net. Thank you and we can't wait to meet you!

post_text: Hey Fort Osage family....history was made today. Haley Ward becomes the first girl state champion in Fort Osage wrestling history this evening. She wins her state championship match by fall over Kaylie Dow (Plattsburg), finishing her freshman season with a perfect 36-0 final record. #fortproud
